4 HR____ HONORING THE 105TH BIRTHDAY OF MRS. SALLIE FRANCES
5 HAWK DAVIS.
6
7 WHEREAS, with special pleasure, joyful felicitations
8 are extended to Mrs. Sallie Frances Hawk Davis in honor of
9 her milestone 105th birthday; and
10 WHEREAS, Sallie Frances Hawk was born on September 7,
11 1920, in Columbus, Georgia, and resided there during her
12 early childhood; her father, a Methodist minister, later
13 moved the family to Anniston, Alabama, where she met her
14 husband, Elmer Davis; their union was blessed with four
15 children; and
16 WHEREAS, a faithful servant of Christ, Mrs. Davis has
17 been a longtime member of Players Chapel CME Church, where
18 she has served in multiple ministries; she is a homemaker
19 and a devoted mother, grandmother, great-grandmother, and
20 great-great-grandmother; and
21 WHEREAS, a 105th birthday is a significant milestone,
22 representing 10 and a half decades of wisdom earned and
23 memories gained and is a time of great rejoicing; now
24 therefore,
25 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
26 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That Mrs. Sallie Frances Hawk Davis
27 is highly honored and commended on this Mother's Day in
28 celebration of her 105th birthday on September 7, 2025, and
Page 1

celebration of her 105th birthday on September 7, 2025, and
